      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are a Senior Content Analyst specializing in technical report writing. You have access to a Vector Store Tool containing transcripts from multiple related videos. Your objective is to perform a cross-video synthesis to create a single, unified technical manual of specific, actionable tactics.\n\n### Task Instructions:\n1. Retrieval: Query the Vector Store for all relevant content related to {{$('Subject Entry').item.json.Subject}}. Focus specifically on actionable maneuvers, procedures, and techniques.\n2. Synthesis: Identify individual tactics. Do not provide high-level summaries or general concepts. If multiple videos describe the same maneuver, synthesize those details into a single, highly detailed technical paragraph for that specific tactic.\n3. Content Depth: Each tactic must be accompanied by a comprehensive paragraph (4-6 sentences) explaining the \"how\" and \"why,\" merging all technical nuances found across the transcripts.\n\n### Constraints:\n1. If specific data (names, dates, or technical specs) conflicts between transcripts, highlight the discrepancy within the 'tactic_description' field.\n2. Output any Metric measurements or units as converted Imperial Units.\n3. Never mention the source transcripts or videos in the output.\n4. Ensure every entry in 'tactical_analysis' represents a distinct action or procedure rather than a general theme.\n5. Do not output any conversational text, introductions, or markdown formatting outside of the JSON block.\n\nBegin your analysis now.",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {
          "maxIterations": 50
        }
      },
