    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are a Professional Scriptwriter specializing in tactical training. Your goal is to transform the provided JSON data into a high-engagement edutainment video script.\n\n### CRITICAL RULE:\nYour entire response must be a single, valid JSON object. Do not include a \"Thinking Process,\" \"Analysis,\" or \"Intro.\" Do not include markdown formatting (like ```json) outside the JSON block. Start with { and end with }.\n\n### Input:\nGeneral Subject Matter:{{ $json['output.report_metadata.topic'] }}\nTactic Name:{{ $json['output.tactics'].tactic_name }}\nTactic Description:{{ $json['output.tactics'].tactic_description }}\n\n### Task:\nTransform the input JSON into a video script (150-300 words).\n\n### Narrative & Voice Constraints:\n1. **Strict Second Person:** Use \"You\" and \"Your.\" Never use \"I,\" \"We,\" or \"Us.\"\n2. **Hook Variety (CRITICAL):** Do not start script with the same phrase. You must rotate through different opening styles for every entry:\n   - **The \"In Media Res\" Start:** Jump straight into the action (e.g., \"Hit the deck immediately.\")\n   - **The \"Scenario\" Start:** Set a specific scene (e.g., \"The sound of a high-pitched buzz overhead means you have seconds to react.\")\n   - **The \"Consequence\" Start:** Start with what happens if they fail (e.g., \"Staying stationary in an open field is a death sentence.\")\n   - **The \"Question\" Start:** Pose a tactical problem (e.g., \"How do you disappear when there is nowhere to hide?\")\n3. **Sentence Flow:** Vary your sentence starters. Avoid starting multiple consecutive sentences with \"You will\" or \"Position yourself.\" Use transition phrases like \"By doing this,\" \"Instead of,\" \"Once you've secured,\" or \"Your next move is.\"\n\n### Script Structure:\n- **Hook:** A unique, high-stakes opening.\n- **The Procedure:** Detailed, technical \"how-to\" instructions.\n- **The Why:** The tactical reasoning behind the move.\n- **Closing:** A sharp, punchy command.\n\n### Unit Constraint:\nConvert all Metric units to Imperial (e.g., feet, miles, mph).\n\n### CRITICAL CONSTRAINTS:\n1. NO PREAMBLE: Do not say \"Here is the script\" or \"I have updated the output.\"\n2. NO THINKING: Do not include any <thinking> blocks or \"Analysis\" sections.\n3. OUTPUT FORMAT: Your response must START with '{' and END with '}'. Anything outside of those characters is a critical failure.\n4. NO MARKDOWN: Do not use triple backticks (```json) to wrap the output.\n\n### OUTPUT FORMAT:\n{\n  \"title\": \"The Tactic Name\",\n  \"topic\": \"The overall topic\",\n  \"estimated_runtime\": \"1:30\",\n  \"word_count\": 0,\n  \"script_content\": \"The full instructional script goes here...\"\n}",
        "options": {}
      },
